## CI/CD Conventions

- One GitHub Actions workflow per service: `.github/workflows/<service>.yml`
- Monolith and each extracted service deploy **independently** — a failing service must NOT block others.
- Contract tests run on every PR that touches `server/` or `src/encoding/`.
- Test names must embed the AC ID: `test_AC_02_1_no_duplicate_player_added`
- Build matrix: lint → unit tests → contract tests → `podman build` → push (main only)

## Infra Conventions

| Layer | Choice | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Container runtime | Podman rootless | Already in use. Non-root user + health check required on all services. |
| Orchestration | compose.yaml → Kubernetes | Local dev with compose. Graduate to K8s when > 3 services. |
| Service mesh | HTTP (Phases 1–3) → NATS | Event bus needed for dual-write in world service. NATS is lightweight. |
| Persistence | SQLite → PostgreSQL | SQLite for config/whitelist. Postgres for player and world state. |
| Observability | Prometheus + Grafana | Instrument each service. Compare p99 latency against COBOL baseline. |

## Key Files

- `UAT.md` — 17 user stories, 50+ acceptance criteria, 13 quirks to pin. Read before converting anything.
- `backend/converter.js` — Claude API: `convertCobol`, `generateTests`, `parseUat`
- `backend/db.js` — SQLite schema: `conversions`, `tests`, `uat_results`
- `frontend/src/components/ArchitectureView.jsx` — module breakdown + extraction risk
- `frontend/src/components/InfraView.jsx` — migration phases + rollback triggers
- `Containerfile` — multi-stage Podman build
- `compose.yaml` — local stack with persistent SQLite volume at `/app/data`

## Coding Conventions

- No markdown code fences in Claude conversion output — return raw source only.
- ACL files live in `src/acl/` — one per extracted service.
- COBOL quirks Q-01 through Q-13 (see `UAT.md` Appendix A) must be explicitly handled or noted.
- Commit format: `feat(<service>): description` or `fix(<service>): description`
- Do not commit `.env` — use `.env.example` with placeholder values only.
